\frac{dy}{dx}=\frac{y+x-2}{y+x-4}
y=\ln|x+y-3|+x+A
3=y+x
y=3-x
\frac{dy}{dx}=\frac{y+x-2}{y+x-4},
y=3-x\Rightarrow y+x-2=1 \text{ and } y+x-4=-1
y^\prime =-1
-1=\frac{1}{-1}
y(x)=3-x
u=y+x-4\\u'=y'+1\\y'=u'-1\\ \frac{dy}{dx}=\frac{y+x-2}{y+x-4}\rightarrow \overset{u=y+x-4}{\rightarrow}\\ u'-1=\frac{u+2}{u}\\ u'=1+\frac{u+2}{u}\\ \frac{du}{dx}=\frac{2u+2}{u}\\ \frac{du}{\frac{2u+2}{u}}=dx\\ \int \frac{u}{2u+2}=\int dx
